The paper deals with predictive models and their adaptation to non-stationary data sources, which is a common problem in machine learning. The focus is on unsupervised learning, which suggests a connection to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of numerical evaluations on both synthetic and real data, which suggests a connection to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of predictive models and their adaptation to non-stationary data sources also suggests a connection to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions the use of image data, which suggests a connection to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the use of iterative algorithms and numerical evaluations suggests a connection to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
